texts.text: >In the venue's training room...
All participants, please use this room.
We'll contact you once everything is ready.
It starts in a few hours. I should rehearse my retirement speech.
There ya are.
Greetings, ex-champ. Let's put our best foot forward, yeah?
...Yeah sure.
Ouch, someone's cranky.
Why'd you even enter a tournament like this?
Doncha know what they're sayin' 'bout it? Everyone here...
...is a streamer or wannabe punk. Even the ex-pros are bad news.
It's a narcissist's wet dream.
But if you're here, you must be one of us, too. *Chuckle*
...If you're done yappin' then scram.
'Scuse me?
You ain't shit, bro.
If that's how it is, we'll settle this before we hit the ring.
(So, it's this kind of tournament. I'm already finished.)
Put 'em up, Kouki! Let's do this—
*Scream*
>All eyes in the venue turn toward the scream beyond the door.
>It opens to reveal...
So, these are the competitors for my festival?
Huh?! What is THAT?
A-A participant, maybe? Like a pro wrestler...
You're...
Listen well. My name is Indrajit.
Strong bodies like yours are perfect for my ritual ceremony.
Surrender quietly. Unless you want to end up like HIM.
>Indrajit tosses the grotesque corpse of a man.
Eek!
Hey... You gotta be kiddin' me...
(A real demon! So, this is Indrajit...)
Hmph. No protest? You all are strong of body but weak of heart.
Well, no matter. Let us begin—
Go! Beat the crap outta him!
What?!
>A demon ally blasts Indrajit into the wall.
Are you okay, Kouki?!
Everyone... Why are you...?
Our demon allies felt a massive power and led us here.
Would've been harder to sneak in had he not killed the guards.
We meet again. You Liberators never learn, do you?
Damn straight. It's payback time!
>The ally demons quickly surround Indrajit.
Oh?
What now, buddy? Can't use your precious arrows at close range.
Let's take him out in one shot!
Now's our chance!
Yeah! Go for broke!
>The demon allies attack Indrajit in unison.
>Then, a sharp blade pierces Indrajit's chest.
Gah!
Yeah, we got him!
Woo-hoo! Take that loser!
>Everyone is visibly relieved.
>However, soon afterward...
*Chuckle*
Where's that voice comin' from?!
Over here.
Ugh!
Megakin!
Your victory is hollow. Did you forget I'm a master of illusion?
I'm also skilled in the art of war. Once the general falls...
The rest scatter like ants.
>The Liberators fight on as they protect the unconscious Megakin.
>However, Indrajit's brutal onslaught is too much.
—I've put up a barrier. One you lowly humans cannot break.
Now I have all the time in the world to sacrifice you.
Shit...
We're just being punked, right?! Somebody's filming this?
Nooo! I don't wanna die!
Damn it all!
If Lord Indra were here, this bastard would never...
Oh? Did I hear "Indra" just now?
I see. Upon closer inspection, I do sense his faint aura on you.
Sadly, those hopes are in vain.
Huh?
What're you talkin' about?
While we fought the other day, I sent a spy after him.
However, Indra noticed and turned the tables on me.
I never received a report...but it didn't matter.
The spy grievously wounded Indra, so I finished him off myself.
You don't mean... Indra is...
Then he didn't show up because...
He was trying to protect us?
Tch...
S-Spare me your lies!
As if Lord Indra would lose to the likes of you!
That again? You're a fool to believe in such a naive weakling.
Shut the hell up! Lord Indra isn't weak!
He's a powerful, unstoppable titan! The greatest of all gods!
Mock him further, and I'll smack that smirk off your face!
Kouki...
You howl in the face of death.
Followers of Indra are unfit to become my sacrifice.
I shall dispatch you first.
Please stop, Indrajit!
Fuck! We gotta do somethin'!
Farewell. Indra awaits you in the afterlife.
Shit! Damn youuuuu!!
I am in no such place.
It... It can't be...
Lord Indra!
"Indrajit",
you will lose that title here!
